Module imagingbook.common
Package imagingbook.common.geometry.ellipse

Class AlgebraicEllipse

java.lang.Object
imagingbook.common.geometry.ellipse.AlgebraicEllipse
public class AlgebraicEllipse extends Object

Represents an algebraic ellipse with the implicit equation A x^2 + B x y + C y^2 + D x + E y + F = 0. Parameters A, ..., F are normalized such that B^2 - 4 A C = -1. Instances are immutable. See Secs. 11.2.1 and F.3.1 for details.

[1] W. Burger, M.J. Burge, Digital Image Processing – An Algorithmic Introduction, 3rd ed, Springer (2022).

      public AlgebraicEllipse(double A, double B, double C, double D, double E, double F)
      Constructor. Creates a AlgebraicEllipse instance by normalizing the supplied parameters [A,...,F] such that d = B^2 - 4 A C = -1. Throws an exception if d is non-negative.
      Parameters:

      B - ellipse parameter B
      C - ellipse parameter C
